---
layout: base.njk
title: Proof of Work Sourcing
description: Weekly research, playbooks, and tool benchmarks from Brendan Williams. Proof of Work Sourcing for ML and robotics hiring. 28 briefs tested. 200+ recruiters trained.
---

<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-tag">
        <span class="hero-tag-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="hero-tag-text">Weekly · Wednesdays 10am London</span>
      </div>
      <h1>
        Proof of Work<br>
        Sourcing for <span class="accent">ML and robotics</span> hiring.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Weekly research, playbooks, and tool benchmarks from <strong>Brendan Williams</strong> —
        AI Sourcing Specialist. Tested across 28 client briefs.
        200+ recruiters trained. Evidence over resumes. <strong>Always free.</strong>
      </p>

      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="/newsletters/" class="btn btn-primary">Read the newsletter</a>
        <a href="/playbooks/" class="btn btn-ghost">Browse playbooks</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="credentials" aria-label="Credentials">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="credentials-grid">
      <div class="credential">
        <div class="credential-num">28</div>
        <div class="credential-label">Client briefs<br>field-tested</div>
      </div>
      <div class="credential">
        <div class="credential-num">200+</div>
        <div class="credential-label">Recruiters<br>trained 2025</div>
      </div>
      <div class="credential">
        <div class="credential-num">~270</div>
        <div class="credential-label">ML engineers<br>sourced @ Cubiq</div>
      </div>
      <div class="credential">
        <div class="credential-num">0→1</div>
        <div class="credential-label">TA function<br>Ellison Institute Oxford</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="manifesto">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="manifesto-grid">
      <div class="manifesto-heading">
        <div class="eyebrow">Methodology</div>
        <h2>Proof of Work<br><span class="accent">Sourcing.</span></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="manifesto-body">
        <p>
          I find ML engineers and robotics specialists through their <strong>code on GitHub</strong>,
          their <strong>papers on arXiv</strong>, and their <strong>models on HuggingFace</strong>.
          Not through CVs or LinkedIn keyword matching.
        </p>
        <div class="callout">
          Evidence over resumes. Technical recognition over mass outreach.
        </div>
        <p>
          Across 2025 I tested the full 2026 AI recruiting stack — Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini,
          Perplexity, Juicebox, SeekOut, hireEZ, LinkedIn Hiring Assistant — on 28 client briefs.
          Response rates on proof-based outreach ran <strong>30–45%</strong>.
          Standard InMail on the same briefs ran <strong>10–25%</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          That gap is what this site is about. The research, the playbooks, and the weekly tool
          reviews from the lab — all free, all public, forever.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="pillars-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">What you get</div>
      <h2>Three things, every Wednesday.</h2>
      <p>
        Not a curated link dump. Original research from the lab, scoped tight,
        anchored to data you can act on the same day.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillars-grid">
      <article class="pillar-card">
        <div class="pillar-num">01 / Automation</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-title">A recipe built in n8n or Make</h3>
        <p class="pillar-desc">
          One automation workflow a week, copy-paste ready. Sourcing, outreach,
          candidate research, pipeline hygiene. Screenshots, JSON, expected time saved.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar-card">
        <div class="pillar-num">02 / Tools</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-title">A head-to-head tool review</h3>
        <p class="pillar-desc">
          Real briefs, real results. hireEZ vs Juicebox on a senior ML search.
          SeekOut vs GitHub direct. Response rates, placement rates, honest verdicts.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar-card">
        <div class="pillar-num">03 / Contrarian</div>
        <h3 class="pillar-title">What AI gets wrong in recruiting</h3>
        <p class="pillar-desc">
          The weekly contrarian take. Where the 2026 tool market breaks, where
          the consensus is off, where direct technical engagement still wins.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="latest">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="latest-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Latest</div>
      <h2>Recent research</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="latest-grid">
      {% set newsletterposts = collections.newsletter | reverse %}
      {% for post in newsletterposts | limit(2) %}
      <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="latest-card">
        <div class="latest-meta">
          {% if post.data.issue %}<span class="latest-issue">Issue {{ post.data.issue }}</span>{% endif %}
          <span class="latest-date">{{ post.data.date | date('%d %b %Y') }}</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="latest-title">{{ post.data.title }}</h3>
        {% if post.data.dek %}<p class="latest-dek">{{ post.data.dek }}</p>{% endif %}
        <span class="latest-arrow">Read →</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}

      {% set playbookposts = collections.playbook | reverse %}
      {% for post in playbookposts | limit(1) %}
      <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="latest-card latest-card-playbook">
        <div class="latest-meta">
          <span class="latest-issue latest-issue-playbook">Playbook</span>
          {% if post.data.readingTime %}<span class="latest-date">{{ post.data.readingTime }}</span>{% endif %}
        </div>
        <h3 class="latest-title">{{ post.data.title }}</h3>
        {% if post.data.dek %}<p class="latest-dek">{{ post.data.dek }}</p>{% endif %}
        <span class="latest-arrow">Read →</span>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

